        <h1>Fixing a Washing Machine Leak</h1>
        <img src="../../../assets/images/pictures/washing_machine.jpg" alt="Washing Machine Leak" style="width:400px; margin:20px 0;">

        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>If your washing machine is leaking water, it could be caused by several factors. Follow this guide to identify and fix common issues safely.</p>

        <h2>Tools Needed</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Screwdriver</li>
            <li>Wrench</li>
            <li>Replacement hoses or clamps</li>
            <li>Bucket and towels</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Step-by-Step Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Unplug the washing machine:</strong> Always ensure safety by disconnecting power.</li>
            <li><strong>Inspect hoses:</strong> Check both inlet and drain hoses for cracks or loose connections.</li>
            <li><strong>Tighten connections:</strong> Use a wrench to secure hose clamps properly.</li>
            <li><strong>Check door seal:</strong> If front-loading, inspect the rubber gasket for tears or debris.</li>
            <li><strong>Replace damaged parts:</strong> Replace any worn hoses, clamps, or seals.</li>
            <li><strong>Run a test cycle:</strong> Fill the machine and check for leaks before resuming normal use.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Tips</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Do not overload the washing machine.</li>
            <li>Keep the floor dry to avoid slipping hazards.</li>
            <li>Regularly inspect hoses and seals to prevent leaks.</li>
        </ul>

